T1  - A Review Essay on the Books of bell hooks: Organizational Diversity Lessons from a Thoughtful Race and Gender Heretic
AU  - Cheng, Cliff
Y1  - 1997/04/01
PY  - 1997
DA  - 1997/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1997.9707154069
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1997.9707154069
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 553
EP  - 564
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a literary criticism of the body of work of bell hooks. The article discusses hooks' theories about white supremacist, capitalist and patriarchal values in society in the context of diversity, multiculturalism, identity politics and contemporary management theory. Books discussed include "Feminist Theory: From Margin to Center," "Ain"t I a Woman: Black Women and Feminism," and "Talking Back: Thinking Feminist, Thinking Black."
AB  - The article presents a literary criticism of the body of work of bell hooks. The article discusses hooks' theories about white supremacist, capitalist and patriarchal values in society in the context of diversity, multiculturalism, identity politics and contemporary management theory. Books discussed include "Feminist Theory: From Margin to Center," "Ain"t I a Woman: Black Women and Feminism," and "Talking Back: Thinking Feminist, Thinking Black."
